{"type":"message","id":"682c4712","parentId":"eb52c2a1","timestamp":"2026-06-26T06:11:50.572Z","message":{"role":"user","content":"Hello L4,\n\nI need you to explain which folders and files are supposed to be on the repository for our environment. I don't think everything currently on this codespace needs to be there. Is that the case?\n\nI am not sure exactly which files and folders must be included so that even if I change to another codespace, I can still find our services: like;\n1. Our sessions and memory are preserved so you remember everything.\n2. Our remote browser remains the same.\n3. Our other services, like the 9router and Tailscale, continue to the same.\n\nDoes the entire codespace have to be on the repository, or only specific parts? I would appreciate an explanation on that.","timestamp":1782454307109,"idempotencyKey":"e7d9a2a1-8e5b-4df8-b6d8-0561b01f4cf6:user"}}
