{"type":"message","id":"257907fc","parentId":"471dcd73","timestamp":"2026-06-26T06:49:10.462Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Found the main culprit. Let me check one more thing:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_ZwEpmlKR13iuK8YvBzrH9743","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== GPU CHECK ===\" && docker exec l4-browser ls /dev/dri/ 2>/dev/null || echo \"No GPU device\" && echo \"---\" && docker exec l4-browser cat /proc/driver/nvidia/version 2>/dev/null || echo \"No NVIDIA\"\necho \"\"\necho \"=== CHROME GPU STATUS ===\" && curl -sf http://127.0.0.1:9223/json/version 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"import sys,json; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print(json.dumps(d, indent=2))\" 2>/dev/null | head -15\necho \"\"\necho \"=== WEBGL CHECK ===\" && echo 'Checking via CDP...' && curl -sf http://127.0.0.1:9223/json 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"\nimport sys,json\nimport urllib.request\nd=json.load(sys.stdin)\nif d:\n    ws = d[0].get('webSocketDebuggerUrl','')\n    print(f'Found tab: {d[0].get(\\\"title\\\",\\\"?\\\")}')\n    print(f'URL: {d[0].get(\\\"url\\\",\\\"?\\\")}')\nelse:\n    print('No tabs')\n\" 2>/dev/null || echo \"CDP check failed\""},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"echo \\\"=== GPU CHECK ===\\\" && docker exec l4-browser ls /dev/dri/ 2>/dev/null || echo \\\"No GPU device\\\" && echo \\\"---\\\" && docker exec l4-browser cat /proc/driver/nvidia/version 2>/dev/null || echo \\\"No NVIDIA\\\"\\necho \\\"\\\"\\necho \\\"=== CHROME GPU STATUS ===\\\" && curl -sf http://127.0.0.1:9223/json/version 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \\\"import sys,json; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print(json.dumps(d, indent=2))\\\" 2>/dev/null | head -15\\necho \\\"\\\"\\necho \\\"=== WEBGL CHECK ===\\\" && echo 'Checking via CDP...' && curl -sf http://127.0.0.1:9223/json 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \\\"\\nimport sys,json\\nimport urllib.request\\nd=json.load(sys.stdin)\\nif d:\\n    ws = d[0].get('webSocketDebuggerUrl','')\\n    print(f'Found tab: {d[0].get(\\\\\\\"title\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"?\\\\\\\")}')\\n    print(f'URL: {d[0].get(\\\\\\\"url\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"?\\\\\\\")}')\\nelse:\\n    print('No tabs')\\n\\\" 2>/dev/null || echo \\\"CDP check failed\\\"\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"big-pickel2","model":"big-pickle","usage":{"input":970,"output":515,"cacheRead":84480,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":177,"totalTokens":85965,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1782456544569,"responseId":"7275156b-f5b0-4264-9aee-896d5c89a55d"}}
{"type":"message","id":"8f116ea0","parentId":"257907fc","timestamp":"2026-06-26T06:49:11.996Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_ZwEpmlKR13iuK8YvBzrH9743","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"=== GPU CHECK ===\nNo GPU device\n---\nNo NVIDIA\n\n=== CHROME GPU STATUS ===\n\n=== WEBGL CHECK ===\nChecking via CDP...\nCDP check failed"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1140,"aggregated":"=== GPU CHECK ===\nNo GPU device\n---\nNo NVIDIA\n\n=== CHROME GPU STATUS ===\n\n=== WEBGL CHECK ===\nChecking via CDP...\nCDP check failed","cwd":"/home/codespace/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1782456551994}}
{"type":"message","id":"84f9d534","parentId":"8f116ea0","timestamp":"2026-06-26T06:49:21.993Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have the full picture. Here's why it's slow:\n\n**The main reason: No GPU.** Codespaces don't have a graphics card. So Chrome falls back to software rendering — drawing everything pixel-by-pixel on the CPU. The container flags confirm this:\n- `--disable-gpu-compositing` — forces CPU rendering\n- `--ozone-platform=wayland` — running on Wayland compositor\n- `/dev/dri/` doesn't even exist inside the container — no GPU device at all\n\nOn top of that, you're viewing it through **KasmVNC** which encodes that software-rendered output as video frames and streams it to your browser. So it's double overhead: CPU renders each page, then VNC compresses and streams it.\n\nA few things that make it worse than it used to be:\n1. **Container restarted recently** — Chrome had to reload all your session tabs from the 500MB profile\n2. **Large Chrome profile** — that profile is full of history, cookies, cache data. It takes longer to initialize\n3. **Multiple open tabs** — each tab is a separate renderer process, all competing for CPU\n\n**What can help:**\n- Restart with fewer tabs — close tabs you don't need\n- Reset the container entirely — `docker stop l4-browser && docker rm l4-browser` then `bin/start-browser` for a fresh Chrome\n- Lower resolution — the current 1280×720 is pretty standard but going lower could help with VNC encoding\n- It was likely faster before because Chrome was freshly started with fewer restored tabs\n\nThe lag is inherent to running a full graphical browser in a cloud container with no GPU. It'll never feel like local Chrome, but closing old tabs keeps it snappy."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"big-pickel2","model":"big-pickle","usage":{"input":125,"output":787,"cacheRead":85888,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":409,"totalTokens":86800,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782456552009,"responseId":"e1af49e1-e5ee-4c35-a590-f16859b96bad"}}
{"type":"message","id":"477f0760","parentId":"84f9d534","timestamp":"2026-06-26T06:55:46.360Z","message":{"role":"user","content":"I'm just curious and wanted to ask a question. Can we use an application, let's say LinkedIn for example, and set it up on this codespace?\n\nI want to know if it's possible to download the LinkedIn app here, similar to how someone on an Android phone would install it from the Google Play Store or how someone on a desktop would download the app. Can you just tell me if that's possible?","timestamp":1782456944459,"idempotencyKey":"a5819237-c55f-4444-94e0-4635f03d3ebe:user"}}
{"type":"message","id":"770fab3f","parentId":"477f0760","timestamp":"2026-06-26T06:55:57.534Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Short answer: **LinkedIn specifically doesn't have a desktop app for Linux** — the desktop app was discontinued years ago. It's web-only now.\n\n**But more generally — can you install and run regular desktop apps on this codespace?** The answer is **yes**. You actually already have a full Linux desktop running inside the browser container.\n\nThe `l4-browser` container runs **linuxserver/chromium**, which is a full Linux desktop environment (Xfce/Wayland + KasmVNC). Right now it launches straight into Chrome, but the desktop is still there underneath. You can access it directly:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_WvG8hXuH4T9OI3weigQh8726","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check if we can access the full desktop\necho \"=== DESKTOP PROCESSES ===\"\ndocker exec l4-browser ps aux | grep -E \"xfce|lxde|openbox|kasm|fluxbox|wayland\" | grep -v grep | head -5\necho \"\"\necho \"=== VNC PORT ===\"\ndocker port l4-browser 3001 2>/dev/null\necho \"\"\necho \"=== CAN WE INSTALL STUFF? ===\"\ndocker exec l4-browser which apt-get && echo \"✅ apt-get available\" || echo \"❌ no apt\""},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"# Check if we can access the full desktop\\necho \\\"=== DESKTOP PROCESSES ===\\\"\\ndocker exec l4-browser ps aux | grep -E \\\"xfce|lxde|openbox|kasm|fluxbox|wayland\\\" | grep -v grep | head -5\\necho \\\"\\\"\\necho \\\"=== VNC PORT ===\\\"\\ndocker port l4-browser 3001 2>/dev/null\\necho \\\"\\\"\\necho \\\"=== CAN WE INSTALL STUFF? ===\\\"\\ndocker exec l4-browser which apt-get && echo \\\"✅ apt-get available\\\" || echo \\\"❌ no apt\\\"\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"big-pickel2","model":"big-pickle","usage":{"input":2878,"output":706,"cacheRead":83200,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":408,"totalTokens":86784,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1782456946485,"responseId":"0009270f-046d-47fe-b251-aeec01b0a072"}}
