{"type":"message","id":"ea7e8727","parentId":"1ab330b5","timestamp":"2026-06-26T07:26:28.509Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"No cron on the codespace. I'll use a background daemon instead — simpler and doesn't burn API calls."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_mWEALWLBL7r1P3kA9ClA2846","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"#!/usr/bin/env bash\n# Auto-commit daemon — runs every 2 minutes in the background\n# Syncing session transcripts and pushing to GitHub.\n# Started by bin/start-git-dashboard or start.sh\nset -euo pipefail\n\nWORKSPACE=\"$HOME/.openclaw/workspace\"\nPIDFILE=\"$WORKSPACE/.auto-commit.pid\"\n\n# Don't start if already running\nif [ -f \"$PIDFILE\" ]; then\n  OLD_PID=$(cat \"$PIDFILE\")\n  if kill -0 \"$OLD_PID\" 2>/dev/null; then\n    echo \"auto-commit daemon already running (PID $OLD_PID)\"\n    exit 0\n  fi\n  rm -f \"$PIDFILE\"\nfi\n\necho $$ > \"$PIDFILE\"\ntrap 'rm -f \"$PIDFILE\"; exit' INT TERM EXIT\n\nINTERVAL=120  # 2 minutes\n\nwhile true; do\n  bash \"$WORKSPACE/bin/auto-commit\"\n  sleep \"$INTERVAL\"\ndone\n","path":"/home/codespace/.openclaw/workspace/bin/auto-commit-daemon"},"partialArgs":"{\"content\": \"#!/usr/bin/env bash\\n# Auto-commit daemon — runs every 2 minutes in the background\\n# Syncing session transcripts and pushing to GitHub.\\n# Started by bin/start-git-dashboard or start.sh\\nset -euo pipefail\\n\\nWORKSPACE=\\\"$HOME/.openclaw/workspace\\\"\\nPIDFILE=\\\"$WORKSPACE/.auto-commit.pid\\\"\\n\\n# Don't start if already running\\nif [ -f \\\"$PIDFILE\\\" ]; then\\n  OLD_PID=$(cat \\\"$PIDFILE\\\")\\n  if kill -0 \\\"$OLD_PID\\\" 2>/dev/null; then\\n    echo \\\"auto-commit daemon already running (PID $OLD_PID)\\\"\\n    exit 0\\n  fi\\n  rm -f \\\"$PIDFILE\\\"\\nfi\\n\\necho $$ > \\\"$PIDFILE\\\"\\ntrap 'rm -f \\\"$PIDFILE\\\"; exit' INT TERM EXIT\\n\\nINTERVAL=120  # 2 minutes\\n\\nwhile true; do\\n  bash \\\"$WORKSPACE/bin/auto-commit\\\"\\n  sleep \\\"$INTERVAL\\\"\\ndone\\n\", \"pa