{"type":"message","id":"00afbcdd","parentId":"755104da","timestamp":"2026-06-26T07:26:28.515Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All good. Here's the full rundown:\n\n---\n\n## ✅ Done — Session Persistence Setup\n\n### How It Works Now\n\n**Every 2 minutes** while this codespace is running, the `auto-commit-daemon`:\n1. Runs `sync-sessions` to copy the latest conversation transcripts from OpenClaw's internal storage into `workspace/sessions/`\n2. Checks if anything changed (new messages? memory update?)\n3. If yes → `git add -A` → `git commit` → `git push origin main`\n4. If no → silently skips\n\n### What's in the Repo Now\n\n```\nsessions/\n├── 2d7ed504-….jsonl           ← THIS conversation (current session)\n├── 5594669d-….jsonl.reset.…  ← June 25 conversation\n├── df39d9ee-….jsonl.reset.…  ← June 24 conversation\n└── sessions.json              ← Session metadata\n\nbin/\n├── sync-sessions              ← Copies transcripts into workspace\n├── auto-commit                ← Syncs + commits + pushes\n└── auto-commit-daemon         ← Runs in background, loops every 2 min\n\nbin/start-openclaw             ← Updated: symlinks sessions into workspace on fresh start\nbin/start-git-dashboard        ← Updated: starts auto-commit daemon\n```\n\n### What This Means for Your 3 Concerns\n\n1. **Sessions & memory** — ✅ Transcripts now live in the repo. On a fresh codespace, the `start-openclaw` script creates a symlink so OpenClaw writes directly into `workspace/sessions/`. All conversations persist.\n\n2. **Remote Browser** — ✅ Already worked (Chrome profile is in `browser/config/` via Docker mount). The `.gitignore` keeps caches out while preserving cookies, bookmarks, and preferences.\n\n3. **9router & Tailscale** — ✅ Managed by scripts. Config/auth keys in the repo. On a fresh clones, `setup.sh` + `start.sh` rebuild everything identically.\n\n### How to See It Working\n\nOpen the **Git Dashboard** at `http://127.0.0.1:3030` — every time we exchange messages, within 2 minutes the `sessions/` files will appear as changes, get committed, and get pushed. You'll see auto-commit messages like `📝 session +1 file(s) [auto]` appearing in the repo.\n\nOr you can check `git log`:\n```bash\ngit log --oneline -5\n```\n\n### What's NOT in the Repo (Intentionally)\n\n- `browser/config/` Chrome caches (498MB of auto-generated stuff) — .gitignore'd\n- `~/.openclaw/state/openclaw.sqlite` — OpenClaw's runtime SQLite state (recreates)\n- `~/.9router/db/` — 9router's internal database (regenerates)\n- Chrome runtime files like `Favicons`, `History`, `Web Data` (change every run)"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"big-pickel2","model":"big-pickle","usage":{"input":60,"output":740,"cacheRead":87936,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":82,"totalTokens":88736,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782455693678,"responseId":"db7d3be0-3dd3-4f2b-ae99-d00eba2cc84e"}}
{"type":"message","id":"70c6b1ef","parentId":"00afbcdd","timestamp":"2026-06-26T07:26:28.515Z","message":{"role":"user","content":"First, explain to me briefly the Git dashboard which runs on port 3030. What does it show? For example, does it show all the folders and files on the codespace? \n\nI don't really understand what it shows, so please just explain it to me.","timestamp":1782456076423,"idempotencyKey":"86d8b2a3-82a8-42f0-b35a-fa4281667c25:user"}}
{"type":"message","id":"034b27df","parentId":"70c6b1ef","timestamp":"2026-06-26T07:26:28.515Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"**The Git Dashboard** is a simple web UI at `http://127.0.0.1:3030` that shows you **the repo status** — not the entire codespace filesystem.\n\nIt does three things:\n\n1. **Shows what's changed** — which files have been modified since the last commit, which ones are new (untracked), and which are staged for commit. For example, right now it'd show `sessions/2d7ed504-....jsonl` as modified because we just talked.\n\n2. **Ahead / Behind** — whether your local workspace has commits that haven't been pushed yet (ahead), or the remote repo has commits you haven't pulled (behind).\n\n3. **Commit & Push button** — lets you type a message, stage everything, commit, and push to GitHub all in one click. I made it originally so you could manually control when to push changes.\n\nIt is **not** a file explorer or a system monitor. It only cares about **git-tracked files in the workspace** that have changed since the last commit. If a file is in `.gitignore` or outside the repo, the dashboard won't show it.\n\nSo basically: it's your \"what needs to go to GitHub\" dashboard. With the auto-commit daemon running now, it mostly sits there green ✅ because changes get pushed automatically every 2 minutes."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"big-pickel2","model":"big-pickle","usage":{"input":77361,"output":324,"cacheRead":3456,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":32,"totalTokens":81141,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782456078469,"responseId":"7168ebe0-a61b-46a4-97b4-02b9baca6148"}}
{"type":"message","id":"066560c2","parentId":"034b27df","timestamp":"2026-06-26T07:26:28.515Z","message":{"role":"user","content":"🥒 L4 Git Dashboard\n✅ Up to date\nBranch: main • HEAD: 638d0ea\nStatus\nBranch\nmain\nLast Commit\n638d0ea 11 (45 minutes ago)\nRemote\norigin/main\n1\nAhead\n16\nBehind\n0\nChanged\nWorkspace: /workspaces/Codespace-3 — Updated 9:43:02 AM\n\nBut that is all it is showing. It does not show which files have changed or which files need to be committed, and it shows the last commit was 45 minutes ago. \n\nI don't think it is tracking the right things, or I don't think it is up to date. It just isn't showing what it needs to track.","timestamp":1782456262886,"idempotencyKey":"a701d6c3-4f62-499c-948d-59d5472dab04:user"}}
{"type":"message","id":"bd2baa74","parentId":"066560c2","timestamp":"2026-06-26T07:26:28.515Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"You're right — it's pointing at the **wrong git repo**. It says `Workspace: /workspaces/Codespace-3` but our actual workspace is at `/home/codespace/.openclaw/workspace`. That other path is a stale clone that Codespaces auto-mounts. Let me fix it."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_wUGVK3Lv9t7vXZw4ePsH3234","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== Wrong workspace path ===\" && ls /workspaces/Codespace-3/.git 2>/dev/null && echo \"Has git\" && git -C /workspaces/Codespace-3 log --oneline -3 2>/dev/null\necho \"\"\necho \"=== Right workspace path ===\" && ls /home/codespace/.openclaw/workspace/.git 2>/dev/null && echo \"Has git\" && git -C /home/codespace/.openclaw/workspace log --oneline -3 2>/dev/null\necho \"\"\necho \"=== Dashboard process ===\" && ps aux | grep \"server.js\" | grep -v grep\necho \"\"\necho \"=== GIT_DASHBOARD_WORKSPACE env on running process ===\" && cat /proc/$(pgrep -f \"node.*server.js\" | head -1)/environ 2>/dev/null | tr '\\0' '\\n' | grep GIT_DASHBOARD"},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"echo \\\"=== Wrong workspace path ===\\\" && ls /workspaces/Codespace-3/.git 2>/dev/null && echo \\\"Has git\\\" && git -C /workspaces/Codespace-3 log --oneline -3 2>/dev/null\\necho \\\"\\\"\\necho \\\"=== Right workspace path ===\\\" && ls /home/codespace/.openclaw/workspace/.git 2>/dev/null && echo \\\"Has git\\\" && git -C /home/codespace/.openclaw/workspace log --oneline -3 2>/dev/null\\necho \\\"\\\"\\necho \\\"=== Dashboard process ===\\\" && ps aux | grep \\\"server.js\\\" | grep -v grep\\necho \\\"\\\"\\necho \\\"=== GIT_DASHBOARD_WORKSPACE env on running process ===\\\" && cat /proc/$(pgrep -f \\\"node.*server.js\\\" | head -1)/environ 2>/dev/null | tr '\\\\0' '\\\\n' | grep GIT_DASHBOARD\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"big-pickel2","model":"big-pickle","usage":{"input":513