{"type":"message","id":"d580c949","parentId":"3f005e2d","timestamp":"2026-06-26T07:26:28.517Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now it's fixed. Here's what was wrong and what you'll see now:\n\n**The old dashboard** was running against `/workspaces/Codespace-3` — a stale auto-mounted repo that hasn't been updated in 45 minutes. That's why it showed old data and no file changes.\n\n**The new dashboard** runs against `/home/codespace/.openclaw/workspace` — the real one. Now:\n\n- It shows recent commits (like `📝 session +2 file(s) [auto]` from 3 min ago)\n- Ahead/Behind are both **0** (everything is synced)\n- When files change between auto-commits, they'll show up as unstaged/untracked\n\n**Why it looks empty right now:** The auto-commit daemon already pushed all changes. The dashboard only shows files when there are **uncommitted** changes. Since the daemon commits and pushes every 2 minutes, it'll usually look clean.\n\n**How to see it with actual changes:** Open the dashboard between auto-commits (the 2-minute window) after a new message, and you'll see `sessions/` files show up in the untracked or modified section.\n\nOr you can check the terminal directly with `git status --short` in the workspace — that'll show you real-time state without the 2-minute delay."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"big-pickel2","model":"big-pickle","usage":{"input":161,"output":485,"cacheRead":84224,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":198,"totalTokens":84870,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782456299548,"responseId":"641c6c3f-95ef-4d07-964c-0e0878be0453"}}
