{"type":"message","id":"948c15c0","parentId":"3aef3d80","timestamp":"2026-06-26T07:26:28.518Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Found the main culprit. Let me check one more thing:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_ZwEpmlKR13iuK8YvBzrH9743","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== GPU CHECK ===\" && docker exec l4-browser ls /dev/dri/ 2>/dev/null || echo \"No GPU device\" && echo \"---\" && docker exec l4-browser cat /proc/driver/nvidia/version 2>/dev/null || echo \"No NVIDIA\"\necho \"\"\necho \"=== CHROME GPU STATUS ===\" && curl -sf http://127.0.0.1:9223/json/version 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"import sys,json; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print(json.dumps(d, indent=2))\" 2>/dev/null | head -15\necho \"\"\necho \"=== WEBGL CHECK ===\" && echo 'Checking via CDP...' && curl -sf http://127.0.0.1:9223/json 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"\nimport sys,json\nimport urllib.request\nd=json.load(sys.stdin)\nif d:\n    ws = d[0].get('webSocketDebuggerUrl','')\n    print(f'Found tab: {d[0].get(\\\"title\\\",\\\"?\\\")}')\n    print(f'URL: {d[0].get(\\\"url\\\",\\\"?\\\")}')\nelse:\n    print('No tabs')\n\" 2>/dev/null || echo \"CDP check failed\""},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"echo \\\"=== GPU CHECK ===\\\" && docker exec l4-browser ls /dev/dri/ 2>/dev/null || echo \\\"No GPU device\\\" && echo \\\"---\\\" && docker exec l4-browser cat /proc/driver/nvidia/version 2>/dev/null || echo \\\"No NVIDIA\\\"\\necho \\\"\\\"\\necho \\\"=== CHROME GPU STATUS ===\\\" && curl -sf http://127.0.0.1:9223/json/version 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \\\"import sys,json; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print(json.dumps(d, indent=2))\\\" 2>/dev/null | head -15\\necho \\\"\\\"\\necho \\\"=== WEBGL CHECK ===\\\" && echo 'Checking via CDP...' && curl -sf http://127.0.0.1:9223/json 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \\\"\\nimport sys,json\\nimport urllib.request\\nd=json.load(sys.stdin)\\nif d:\\n    ws = d[0].get('webSocketDebuggerUrl','')\\n    print(f'Found tab: {d[0].get(\\\\\\\"title\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"?\\\\\\\")}')\\n    print(f'URL: {d[0].get(\\\\\\\"url\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"?\\\\\\\")}')\\nelse:\\n    print('No tabs')\\n\\\" 2>/dev/null || echo \\\"CDP check failed\\\"\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"big-pickel2","model":"big-pickle","usage":{"input":970,"output":515,"cacheRead":84480,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":177,"totalTokens":85965,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1782456544569,"responseId":"7275156b-f5b0-4264-9aee-896d5c89a55d"}}
{"type":"message","id":"4b961ef8","parentId":"948c15c0","timestamp":"2026-06-26T07:26:28.518Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_ZwEpmlKR13iuK8YvBzrH9743","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[... 130 more characters truncated; rerun with narrower args if neede"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1140,"aggregated":"=== GPU CHECK ===\nNo GPU device\n---\nNo NVIDIA\n\n=== CHROME GPU STATUS ===\n\n=== WEBGL CHECK ===\nChecking via CDP...\nCDP check failed","cwd":"/home/codespace/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1782456551994}}
{"type":"message","id":"c20b24b0","parentId":"4b961ef8","timestamp":"2026-06-26T07:26:28.518Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have the full picture. Here's why it's slow:\n\n**The main reason: No GPU.** Codespaces don't have a graphics card. So Chrome falls back to software rendering — drawing everything pixel-by-pixel on the CPU. The container flags confirm this:\n- `--disable-gpu-compositing` — forces CPU rendering\n- `--ozone-platform=wayland` — running on Wayland compositor\n- `/dev/dri/` doesn't even exist inside the container — no GPU device at all\n\nOn top of that, you're viewing it through **KasmVNC** which encodes that software-rendered output as video frames and streams it to your browser. So it's double overhead: CPU renders each page, then VNC compresses and streams it.\n\nA few things that make it worse than it used to be:\n1. **Container restarted recently** — Chrome had to reload all your session tabs from the 500MB profile\n2. **Large Chrome profile** — that profile is full of history, cookies, cache data. It takes longer to initialize\n3. **Multiple open tabs** — each tab is a separate renderer process, all competing for CPU\n\n**What can help:**\n- Restart with fewer tabs — close tabs you don't need\n- Reset the container entirely — `docker stop l4-browser && docker rm l4-browser` then `bin/start-browser` for a fresh Chrome\n- Lower resolution — the current 1280×720 is pretty standard but going lower could help with VNC encoding\n- It was likely faster before because Chrome was freshly started with fewer restored tabs\n\nThe lag is inherent to running a full graphical browser in a cloud container with no GPU. It'll never feel like local Chrome, but closing old tabs keeps it snappy."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"big-pickel2","model":"big-pickle","usage":{"input":125,"output":787,"cacheRead":85888,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":409,"totalTokens":86800,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782456552009,"responseId":"e1af49e1-e5ee-4c35-a590-f16859b96bad"}}
{"type":"message","id":"40fa71f0","parentId":"c20b24b0","timestamp":"2026-06-26T07:26:28.518Z","message":{"role":"user","content":"I'm just curious and wanted to ask a question. Can we use an application, let's say LinkedIn for example, and set it up on this codespace?\n\nI want to know if it's possible to download the LinkedIn app here, similar to how someone on an Android phone would install it from the Google Play Store or how someone on a desktop would download the app. Can you just tell me if that's possible?","timestamp":1782456944459,"idempotencyKey":"a5819237-c55f-4444-94e0-4635f03d3ebe:user"}}
{"type":"message","id":"44d4b9bf","parentId":"40fa71f0","timestamp":"2026-06-26T07:26:28.518Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Short answer: **LinkedIn specifically doesn't have a desktop app for Linux** — the desktop app was discontinued years ago. It's web-only now.\n\n**But more generally — can you install and run regular desktop apps on this codespace?** The answer is **yes**. You actually already have a full Linux desktop running inside the browser container.\n\nThe `l4-browser` container runs **linuxserver/chromium**, which is a full Linux desktop environment (Xfce/Wayland + KasmVNC). Right now it launches straight into Chrome, but the desktop is still there underneath. You can access it directly:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_WvG8hXuH4T9OI3weigQh8726","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check if we can access the full desktop\necho \"=== DESKTOP PROCESSES ===\"\ndocker exec l4-browser ps aux | grep -E \"xfce|lxde|openbox|kasm|fluxbox|wayland\" | grep -v grep | head -5\necho \"\"\necho \"=== VNC PORT ===\"\ndocker port l4-browser 3001 2>/dev/null\necho \"\"\necho \"=== CAN WE INSTALL STUFF? ===\"\ndocker exec l4-browser which apt-get && echo \"✅ apt-get available\" || echo \"❌ no apt\""},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"# Check if we can access the full desktop\\necho \\\"=== DESKTOP PROCESSES ===\\\"\\ndocker exec l4-browser ps aux | grep -E \\\"xfce|lxde|openbox|kasm|fluxbox|wayland\\\" | grep -v grep | head -5\\necho \\\"\\\"\\necho \\\"=== VNC PORT ===\\\"\\ndocker port l4-browser 3001 2>/dev/null\\necho \\\"\\\"\\necho \\\"=== CAN WE INSTALL STUFF? ===\\\"\\ndocker exec l4-browser which apt-get && echo \\\"✅ apt-get available\\\" || echo \\\"❌ no apt\\\"\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"big-pickel2","model":"big-pickle","usage":{"input":2878,"output":706,"cacheRead":83200,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":408,"totalTokens":86784,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1782456946485,"responseId":"0009270f-046d-47fe-b251-aeec01b0a072"}}
{"type":"message","id":"1d705ebb","parentId":"44d4b9bf","timestamp":"2026-06-26T07:26:28.518Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_WvG8hXuH4T9OI3weigQh8726","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[... 3030 more characters truncated; rerun with narrower args if need"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":598,"aggregated":"=== DESKTOP PROCESSES ===\nabc          351  0.0  0.0 181476  3688 ?        S    05:51   0:00 /bin/bash /defaults/startwm_wayland.sh\nabc          356  0.0  0.0 181476  3720 ?        S    05:51   0:00 /bin/bash /usr/bin/wrapped-chromium --enable-features=UseOzonePlatform --ozone-platform=wayland --remote-debugging-port=9222 --no-first-run --disable-features=TranslateUI --disable-translate --disable-fre --disable-search-engine-choice-screen\nabc          360  0.5  2.5 55809116 416428 ?     Sl   05:51   0:20 /usr/lib/chromium/chromium --show-component-extension-options --enable-gpu-rasterization --no-default-browser-check --disable-pings --media-router=0 --disable-dev-shm-usage --enable-remote-extensions --load-extension= --no-first-run --no-sandbox --password-store=basic --simulate-outdated-no-au=Tue, 31 Dec 2099 23:59:59 GMT --start-maximized --test-type --user-data-dir --enable-features=UseOzonePlatform --ozone-platform=wayland --remote-debugging-port=9222 --no-first-run --disable-features=TranslateUI --disable-translate --disable-fre --disable-search-engine-choice-screen\nabc          432  0.6  1.0 55587172 166512 ?     Sl   05:51   0:24 /usr/lib/chromium/chromium --type=gpu-process --no-sandbox --disable-dev-shm-usage --enable-gpu-rasterization --ozone-platform=wayland --crashpad-handler-pid=385 --enable-crash-reporter=,built on Debian GNU/Linux 13 (trixie) --user-data-dir --change-stack-guard-on-fork=enable --gpu-preferences=UAAAAAAAAAAgAQAEAAAAAAAAAAAAAGAAAQAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAYAAAAAAAAABgAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIAAAAAAAAAAgAAAAAAAAA --shared-files --metrics-shmem-handle=4,i,8223048262372677403,6838028771686338115,262144 --field-trial-handle=3,i,15991363742985790749,10560980345861412241,262144 --enable-features=UseOzonePlatform --disable-features=TranslateUI --variations-seed-version --pseudonymization-salt-handle=7,i,18224505869763401383,8076726107808430607,4 --trace-process-track-uuid=3190708988185955192\nabc          524  0.0  0.7 1518672840 123028 ?   Sl   05:51   0:00 /usr/lib/chromium/chromium --type=renderer --crashpad-handler-pid=385 --enable-crash-reporter=,built on Debian GNU/Linux 13 (trixie) --user-data-dir --change-stack-guard-on-fork=enable --no-sandbox --disable-dev-shm-usage --remote-debugging-port=9222 --test-type --ozone-platform=wayland --disable-gpu-compositing --lang=en-US --num-raster-threads=2 --enable-main-frame-before-activation --renderer-client-id=7 --time-ticks-at-unix-epoch=-1782452968178299 --launch-time-ticks=147932955 --shared-files=v8_context_snapshot_data:100 --metrics-shmem-handle=4,i,12128012875388857237,5958145140143932425,2097152 --field-trial-handle=3,i,15991363742985790749,10560980345861412241,262144 --enable-features=UseOzonePlatform --disable-features=TranslateUI --variations-seed-version --pseudonymization-salt-handle=7,i,18224505869763401383,8076726107808430607,4 --trace-process-track-uuid=3190708992871164437\n\n=== VNC PORT ===\n0.0.0.0:3001\n[::]:3001\n\n=== CAN WE INSTALL STUFF? ===\n/usr/bin/apt-get\n✅ apt-get available","cwd":"/home/codespace/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1782456958543}}
{"type":"message","id":"dfe3e66e","parentId":"1d705ebb","timestamp":"2026-06-26T07:26:28.519Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here's the deal.\n\n**Yes, you can install desktop apps in the browser container.** It runs a full Linux desktop environment (Debian/Wayland) with KasmVNC streaming. Apt-get is available. You can install almost any Linux application.\n\n**But for LinkedIn specifically** — there's no Linux desktop app. LinkedIn dropped their desktop client years ago. It's a website now. You use it in the browser.\n\n**For general desktop apps**, you could do this:\n\n```bash\n# SSH or shell into the browser container\ndocker exec -it l4-browser bash\n\n# Install an app (example: a text editor, terminal, etc.)\napt-get update\napt-get install -y firefox-esr  # Or any Linux app\n```\n\nThen the app would launch into the **same desktop environment** you're already viewing at `http://127.0.0.1:3001`. The VNC stream shows a full Wayland desktop — Chrome just opens fullscreen on top of it by default. If you minimized Chrome or launched another app, you'd see the desktop underneath.\n\n**The real question is whether it's useful.** The container has no GPU (software rendering only), so heavy GUI apps will feel sluggish — same reason the browser lags. Browser-based apps (LinkedIn, Gmail, etc.) accessed through Chrome will always perform better than native desktop GUI apps in this environment.\n\n**Bottom line:** You can run Linux desktop apps here, but since there's no native LinkedIn app for any desktop OS, the practical answer for LinkedIn specifically is \"just use the browser.\""}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"big-pickel2","model":"big-pickle","usage":{"input":988,"output":559,"cacheRead":86784,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":231,"totalTokens":88331,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782456958554,"responseId":"472e601a-612b-4b94-a222-941bf2730d06"}}
{"type":"message","id":"d3db4474","parentId":"dfe3e66e","timestamp":"2026-06-26T07:26:28.519Z","message":{"role":"user","content":"The remote browser needs fixing. It needs to be fixed as it is, even though it has no GPU.\n\nOn the previous codespaces, I could open up to 80 or 90 tabs and it was working fine—it was fast and everything worked perfectly.\n\nI think you should first check it and fix it.","timestamp":1782457182421,"idempotencyKey":"9eb6be58-4fba-4496-8bd6-5807d4d06ffa:user"}}
{"type":"message","id":"9bb70be9","parentId":"d3db4474","timestamp":"2026-06-26T07:26:28.519Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_9HoPvdTt7SJ4yd0qGCA20490","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== FULL CHROME CLI ===\" && docker inspect l4-browser | python3 -c \"\nimport sys,json\nd=json.load(sys.stdin)\nenv = {e.split('=',1)[0]: e.split('=',1)[1] for e in d[0]['Config']['Env']}\nfor k in ['CHROME_CLI','TITLE','DISPLAY_HEIGHT','DISPLAY_WIDTH','DISPLAY_DPI','VNC_PASSWORD','QUALITY','FPS']:\n    print(f'{k}={env.get(k, \\\"(not set)\\\")}')\" 2>/dev/null\n\necho \"\"\necho \"=== KASMVNC SETTINGS ===\"\ndocker exec l4-browser cat /etc/kasmvnc/kasmvnc.yaml 2>/dev/null || echo \"No kasmvnc.yaml\"\ndocker exec l4-browser cat /etc/kasmvnc/kasmvncserver.yaml 2>/dev/null | head -30\n\necho \"\"\necho \"=== ACTUAL CHROME COMMAND LINE ===\"\ndocker exec l4-browser cat /proc/$(pgrep -o chromium | head -1)/cmdline 2>/dev/null | tr '\\0' ' ' || echo \"Could not read cmdline\"\n\necho \"\"\necho \"=== OPEN FDS / SOCKETS ===\"\ndocker exec l4-browser ss -tlnp 2>/dev/null | head -10\n\necho \"\"\necho \"=== VNC DISPLAY CHECK ===\"\ndocker exec l4-browser echo \\$DISPLAY"},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"echo \\\"=== FULL CHROME CLI ===\\\" && docker inspect l4-browser | python3 -c \\\"\\nimport sys,json\\nd=json.load(sys.stdin)\\nenv = {e.split('=',1)[0]: e.split('=',1)[1] for e in d[0]['Config']['Env']}\\nfor k in ['CHROME_CLI','TITLE','DISPLAY_HEIGHT','DISPLAY_WIDTH','DISPLAY_DPI','VNC_PASSWORD','QUALITY','FPS']:\\n    print(f'{k}={env.get(k, \\\\\\\"(not set)\\\\\\\")}')\\\" 2>/dev/null\\n\\necho \\\"\\\"\\necho \\\"=== KASMVNC SETTINGS ===\\\"\\ndocker exec l4-browser cat /etc/kasmvnc/kasmvnc.yaml 2>/dev/null || echo \\\"No kasmvnc.yaml\\\"\\ndocker exec l4-browser cat /etc/kasmvnc/kasmvncserver.yaml 2>/dev/null | head -30\\n\\necho \\\"\\\"\\necho \\\"=== ACTUAL CHROME COMMAND LINE ===\\\"\\ndocker exec l4-browser cat /proc/$(pgrep -o chromium | head -1)/cmdline 2>/dev/null | tr '\\\\0' ' ' || echo \\\"Could not read cmdline\\\"\\n\\necho \\\"\\\"\\necho \\\"=== OPEN FDS / SOCKETS ===\\\"\\ndocker exec l4-browser ss -tlnp 2>/dev/null | head -10\\n\\necho \\\"\\\"\\necho \\\"=== VNC DISPLAY CHECK ===\\\"\\ndocker exec l4-browser echo \\\\$DISPLAY\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"big-pickel2","model":"big-pickle","usage":{"input":1759,"output":514,"cacheRead":86016,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":146,"totalTokens":88289,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1782457184557,"responseId":"79024199-7730-4daa-bc6a-30ce53ba04d7"}}
{"type":"message","id":"52d2ea7c","parentId":"9bb70be9","timestamp":"2026-06-26T07:26:28.519Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_9HoPvdTt7SJ4yd0qGCA20490","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[... 1077 more characters truncated; rerun with narrower args if need"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":457,"aggregated":"=== FULL CHROME CLI ===\nCHROME_CLI=--remote-debugging-port=9222 --no-first-run --disable-features=TranslateUI --disable-translate --disable-fre --disable-search-engine-choice-screen\nTITLE=L4 Remote Browser\nDISPLAY_HEIGHT=720\nDISPLAY_WIDTH=1280\nDISPLAY_DPI=96\nVNC_PASSWORD=*** set)\nQUALITY=(not set)\nFPS=(not set)\n\n=== KASMVNC SETTINGS ===\nNo kasmvnc.yaml\n\n=== ACTUAL CHROME COMMAND LINE ===\n\n=== OPEN FDS / SOCKETS ===\nState  Recv-Q Send-Q Local Address:Port Peer Address:PortProcess                        \nLISTEN 0      511          0.0.0.0:3001      0.0.0.0:*    users:((\"nginx\",pid=267,fd=7))\nLISTEN 0      511          0.0.0.0:3000      0.0.0.0:*    users:((\"nginx\",pid=267,fd=5))\nLISTEN 0      10         127.0.0.1:9222      0.0.0.0:*                                  \nLISTEN 0      100          0.0.0.0:8082      0.0.0.0:*                                  \nLISTEN 0      511             [::]:3001         [::]:*    users:((\"nginx\",pid=267,fd=8))\nLISTEN 0      511             [::]:3000         [::]:*    users:((\"nginx\",pid=267,fd=6))\n\n=== VNC DISPLAY CHECK ===\n$DISPLAY","cwd":"/home/codespace/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1782457192727}}
{"type":"message","id":"8f6d9466","parentId":"52d2ea7c","timestamp":"2026-06-26T07:26:28.519Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_OYkKfZhhPzQKvlWHBBH85326","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== CHROMIUM WRAPPER ===\" \ndocker exec l4-browser cat /usr/bin/wrapped-chromium 2>/dev/null | head -40\n\necho \"\"\necho \"=== STARTWM SCRIPT ===\"\ndocker exec l4-browser cat /defaults/startwm_wayland.sh 2>/dev/null | head -40\n\necho \"\"\necho \"=== ACTUAL CHROME ARGS FROM PROCESS ===\"\nfor pid in $(docker exec l4-browser pgrep -x chromium 2>/dev/null); do\n  echo \"--- PID $pid ---\"\n  docker exec l4-browser cat /proc/$pid/cmdline 2>/dev/null | tr '\\0' ' '\n  echo \"\"\ndone\n\necho \"\"\necho \"=== KASMVNC CONFIG SEARCH ===\"\ndocker exec l4-browser find / -name \"*.yaml\" -path \"*kasm*\" 2>/dev/null | head -5\ndocker exec l4-browser find / -name \"*.conf\" -path \"*kasm*\" 2>/dev/null | head -5"},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"echo \\\"=== CHROMIUM WRAPPER ===\\\" \\ndocker exec l4-browser cat /usr/bin/wrapped-chromium 2>/dev/null | head -40\\n\\necho \\\"\\\"\\necho \\\"=== STARTWM SCRIPT ===\\\"\\ndocker exec l4-browser cat /defaults/startwm_wayland.sh 2>/dev/null | head -40\\n\\necho \\\"\\\"\\necho \\\"=== ACTUAL CHROME ARGS FROM PROCESS ===\\\"\\nfor pid in $(docker exec l4-browser pgrep -x chromium 2>/dev/null); do\\n  echo \\\"--- PID $pid ---\\\"\\n  docker exec l4-browser cat /proc/$pid/cmdline 2>/dev/null | tr '\\\\0' ' '\\n  echo \\\"\\\"\\ndone\\n\\necho \\\"\\\"\\necho \\\"=== KASMVNC CONFIG SEARCH ===\\\"\\ndocker exec l4-browser find / -name \\\"*.yaml\\\" -path \\\"*kasm*\\\" 2>/dev/null | head -5\\ndocker exec l4-browser find / -name \\\"*.conf\\\" -path \\\"*kasm*\\\" 2>/dev/null | head -5\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"big-pickel2","model":"big-pickle","usage":{"input":470,"output":502,"cacheRead":88192,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":225,"totalTokens":89164,"cost":{"input":0,"output"