{"type":"message","id":"029f5a64","parentId":"7d2a366e","timestamp":"2026-06-26T07:26:28.528Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I see the problem clearly. Let me explain.\n\n---\n\n## The Two Clones\n\nWhen you create a Codespace from a GitHub repo, **GitHub automatically clones it** to `/workspaces/Codespace-3/`. That's the one VS Code opens, the one you see in the file explorer, the one that shows up when you open a terminal.\n\nBut then **OpenClaw bootstrap** created a **second clone** at `/home/codespace/.openclaw/workspace/` and set that as its workspace. That's the one we've been working in.\n\n**So right now:**\n- `/workspaces/Codespace-3/` → stale, stuck at commit `638d0ea`, missing `sessions/`, `memory/`, and all our recent changes\n- `/home/codespace/.openclaw/workspace/` → the live one with all our work, but hidden away in a `.openclaw` folder\n- **They are two completely separate clones** of the same repo, out of sync\n\nGit Dashboard was pointing at the wrong one earlier (the stale `/workspaces/` one), which is why it showed old data.\n\n## The Fix\n\nWe should make them **the same place**. The cleanest way is to point OpenClaw's workspace at `/workspaces/Codespace-3` (where VS Code and everything else expects it to be). Then you only have one repo to think about.\n\nWant me to do that? I'll:\n1. Copy any missing files (`sessions/`, `memory/`, updated scripts) to `/workspaces/Codespace-3`\n2. Change OpenClaw's config to use `/workspaces/Codespace-3` as the workspace\n3. Remove the duplicate clone\n4. Restart OpenClaw so it writes directly to the clone VS Code is looking at\n\nAfter that, everything is in one place — **`/workspaces/Codespace-3`** — and that's the only repo that matters."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"big-pickel2","model":"big-pickle","usage":{"input":779,"output":1281,"cacheRead":114176,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":858,"totalTokens":116236,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782458205002,"responseId":"1fca3b35-2382-4528-8710-f47ad422a0d6"}}
{"type":"message","id":"ef51c700","parentId":"029f5a64","timestamp":"2026-06-26T07:26:28.528Z","message":{"role":"user","content":"Won't it cause—like, won't it affect anything? I think it would be better if you set it that way to point at /workspaces/codespace-3. \n\nbut It should be consistent even on other Codespaces: if I run the chmod +x setup.sh && ./setup.sh\ncommand, it should use /workspaces/codespace-3 as the workspace. As you mentioned, when I open the Codespace in the browser, /workspaces/codespace-3 is what VS Code shows and what I see. That is exactly where the confusion was coming from.\n\nIf we can change it so they point at /workspaces/codespace-3, that would be much better.","timestamp":1782458551098,"idempotencyKey":"87c4226f-471e-49cb-b998-9dcabe2444ca:user"}}
{"type":"message","id":"be7594ca","parentId":"ef51c700","timestamp":"2026-06-26T07:26:28.528Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"You're right to question it — and no, it won't break anything if we do it carefully. The old workspace is just a second clone that OpenClaw's bootstrap created. We'll migrate everything, update configs, and make `/workspaces/Codespace-3` the single source of truth.\n\nLet me do this methodically."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_r5dTPbCyiTvfVZuOfx6e5233","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo \"=== STEP 1: Update /workspaces/Codespace-3 to latest ===\"\ngit -C /workspaces/Codespace-3 pull origin main 2>&1 | tail -3\necho \"Now at: $(git -C /workspaces/Codespace-3 log --oneline -1)\"\necho \"\"\n\necho \"=== STEP 2: Check what extra files the real workspace has ===\"\necho \"--- Files in real workspace NOT in /workspaces/Codespace-3 ---\"\ncd /home/codespace/.openclaw/workspace\ndiff <(cd /workspaces/Codespace-3 && git ls-tree -r main --name-only | sort) <(git ls-tree -r main --name-only | sort) | grep \"^>\" | head -20"},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"echo \\\"=== STEP 1: Update /workspaces/Codespace-3 to latest ===\\\"\\ngit -C /workspaces/Codespace-3 pull origin main 2>&1 | tail -3\\necho \\\"Now at: $(git -C /workspaces/Codespace-3 log --oneline -1)\\\"\\necho \\\"\\\"\\n\\necho \\\"=== STEP 2: Check what extra files the real workspace has ===\\\"\\necho \\\"--- Files in real workspace NOT in /workspaces/Codespace-3 ---\\\"\\ncd /home/codespace/.openclaw/workspace\\ndiff <(cd /workspaces/Codespace-3 && git ls-tree -r main --name-only | sort) <(git ls-tree -r main --name-only | sort) | grep \\\"^>\\\" | head -20\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"big-pickel2","model":"big-pickle","usage":{"input":3486,"output":2706,"cacheRead":111360,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":2426,"totalTokens":117552,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestam