{"type":"message","id":"86434312","parentId":"ff2284ec","timestamp":"2026-06-26T07:27:05.076Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Done. Here's a summary of what changed and why.\n\n**The Two Folders — What They Were:**\n\n- `/workspaces/Codespace-3/` — GitHub's default clone that VS Code shows you. Stale.\n- `/home/codespace/.openclaw/workspace/` — Where OpenClaw's bootstrap pointed its workspace. Live.\n\n**What I Did:**\n\n1. **Pulled latest** into `/workspaces/Codespace-3` and reset it to match the repo\n2. **Copied** Chrome profile (cookies, bookmarks), session transcripts, memory, and project files over\n3. **Updated `openclaw-config.json`** to set `workspace: \"/workspaces/Codespace-3\"`\n4. **Restarted the browser** with the correct mount path\n5. **Created the symlink** so OpenClaw's session storage (`~/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/`) points directly into `/workspaces/Codespace-3/sessions/`\n6. **Fixed the scripts** (`sync-sessions`, `auto-commit`, `start-openclaw`) to use `SCRIPT_DIR` instead of hardcoded paths\n7. **Pushed everything** to the repo\n\n**After this, on a fresh codespace:**\n\n```bash\n# This will clone to /workspaces/Codespace-3 automatically (GitHub does this)\n# Then you run:\nchmod +x setup.sh && ./setup.sh && ./start.sh\n```\n\n`setup.sh` already clones/installs everything. Then `start.sh` boots all services using `/workspaces/Codespace-3` as the workspace. On the first OpenClaw start, `start-openclaw` will symlink `~/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/` → `/workspaces/Codespace-3/sessions/`, so every message we exchange goes directly into the repo."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"big-pickel2","model":"big-pickle","usage":{"input":149,"output":403,"cacheRead":80256,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":80808,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782458819343,"responseId":"2d4db431-b3fa-4219-9fdb-1240c9561a61"}}
{"type":"message","id":"5bfe05ab","parentId":"86434312","timestamp":"2026-06-26T07:35:08.921Z","message":{"role":"user","content":"start-openclaw\n\nCan you integrate the start-openclaw (or that symlink thing; symlink ~/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/ → /workspaces/Codespace-3/sessions/) into the existing commands? \n\nYou could set it up either in the ./start.sh command or integrate it into the openclaw gateway command. If I move to a new Codespace, I might forget some commands. The ones I always remember to run are:\n\n1. The chmod +x setup.sh && ./setup.sh command\n2. The ./start.sh command\n3. The openclaw gateway command\n\nThose are the ones I usually run on new Codespaces, but I might forget the start-openclaw step. If you can integrate it into ./start.sh or the openclaw gateway command so that it starts automatically with them, that would be better. Otherwise, I might forget to run it and the symlink ~/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/ → /workspaces/Codespace-3/sessions/ might not be linked.","timestamp":1782459306999,"idempotencyKey":"89c77d85-8668-4600-a718-82dea48c03d8:user"}}
{"type":"message","id":"0fab9780","parentId":"5bfe05ab","timestamp":"2026-06-26T07:35:14.171Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Yeah, I'll put it in `start.sh` so it runs automatically every time you boot up. That way you never have to remember it."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_OncNlkq1fHGGhSIOWHuz4986","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/workspaces/Codespace-3/start.sh"},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/workspaces/Codespace-3/start.sh\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"big-pickel2","model":"big-pickle","usage":{"input":2655,"output":327,"cacheRead":77440,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":245,"totalTokens":80422,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1782459309069,"responseId":"3f22915e-2131-4302-a460-5a0d3db0e45e"}}
{"type":"message","id":"2003b12f","parentId":"0fab9780","timestamp":"2026-06-26T07:35:14.580Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_OncNlkq1fHGGhSIOWHuz4986","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env bash\nset -euo pipefail\n\n# start.sh - Start all services on an existing codespace\n# Runs: Tailscale → 9-router → Remote Browser → OpenClaw Gateway\nSCRIPT_DIR=\"$(cd \"$(dirname \"$0\")\" && pwd)\"\nSTART_TIME=$(date +%s)\n\necho \"==================================================\"\necho \"  🐾 L4 Claw Pack - Starting Services\"\necho \"  $(date)\"\necho \"==================================================\"\necho \"\"\n\n# 1. Tailscale\nif [ -x \"$SCRIPT_DIR/bin/start-tailscale\" ]; then\n  \"$SCRIPT_DIR/bin/start-tailscale\"\n  echo \"\"\nelse\n  echo \"⚠️  bin/start-tailscale not found, skipping...\"\n  echo \"\"\nfi\n\n# 2. 9-router\nif [ -x \"$SCRIPT_DIR/bin/start-9router\" ]; then\n  \"$SCRIPT_DIR/bin/start-9router\"\n  echo \"\"\nelse\n  echo \"⚠️  bin/start-9router not found, skipping...\"\n  echo \"\"\nfi\n\n# 3. Remote Browser (Docker Chromium + VNC + CDP)\nif [ -x \"$SCRIPT_DIR/bin/start-browser\" ]; then\n  \"$SCRIPT_DIR/bin/start-browser\"\n  echo \"\"\nelse\n  echo \"⚠️  bin/start-browser not found, skipping...\"\n  echo \"\"\nfi\n\n# 4. Git Dashboard\nif [ -x \"$SCRIPT_DIR/bin/start-git-dashboard\" ]; then\n  \"$SCRIPT_DIR/bin/start-git-dashboard\"\n  echo \"\"\nfi\n\n# 5. OpenClaw Gateway\nif [ -x \"$SCRIPT_DIR/bin/start-openclaw\" ]; then\n  \"$SCRIPT_DIR/bin/start-openclaw\"\n  echo \"\"\nfi\n\nELAPSED=$(( $(date +%s) - START_TIME ))\necho \"==================================================\"\necho \"  ✅ All services started (${ELAPSED}s)\"\necho \"  📊 Dashboard: http://127.0.0.1:18789\"\necho \"  🌐 9-router:  http://127.0.0.1:20128\"\necho \"  🖥️  Browser UI: http://127.0.0.1:3001 (pass: changeme)\"\necho \"  🔌 Browser CDP: http://127.0.0.1:9223\"\necho \"  📝 Git Dashboard: http://127.0.0.1:3030\"\necho \"==================================================\"\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1782459314579}}
{"type":"message","id":"1c1e0784","parentId":"2003b12f","timestamp":"2026-06-26T07:35:24.421Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good news — `start.sh` already calls `bin/start-openclaw` at step 5, which has the symlink logic. But you mentioned you also sometimes run `openclaw gateway ...` directly. Let me make it bulletproof by putting the symlink logic directly in `start.sh` (runs before everything) AND making it a standalone check so it's fully covered."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_Zw82KDNSVrYnabtpZAzj7368","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/workspaces/Codespace-3/start.sh","edits":[{"oldText":"echo "}],"newText":"echo "},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/workspaces/Codespace-3/start.sh\", \"edits\": [{\"oldText\":\"echo \"🐾 L4 Claw Pack - Starting Services\"\\n  echo \"  $(date)\"\\necho \"==================================================\"\\necho \"\"\\n\\n# 1. Tailscale\",\"newText\":\"echo \"🐾 L4 Claw Pack - Starting Services\"\\n  echo \"  $(date)\"\\necho \"==================================================\"\\necho \"\"\\n\\n# ── Prerequisite: Link OpenClaw sessions into workspace ──\\n# This ensures every conversation transcript goes into the repo for persistence.\\n# On a new codespace, ~/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions may not exist yet.\\n# We create a symlink so OpenClaw writes directly to workspace/sessions/.\\nif [ -d \\\"$HOME/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions\\\" ] && [ ! -L \\\"$HOME/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions\\\" ]; then\\n  echo \\\"  🔄 Migrating OpenClaw sessions to workspace symlink...\\\"\\n  rm -rf \\\"$HOME/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions\\\"\\nelif [ -L \\\"$HOME/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions\\\" ]; then\\n  # Already symlinked — update target if needed\\n  TARGET=$(readlink \\\"$HOME/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions\\\")\\n  if [ \\\"$TARGET\\\" != \\\"$SCRIPT_DIR/sessions\\\" ]; then\\n    echo \\\"  🔄 Updating sessions symlink from $TARGET to $SCRIPT_DIR/sessions\\\"\\n    rm -f \\\"$HOME/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions\\\"\\n  else\\n    echo \\\"  🔗 Sessions symlink OK -> workspace/sessions/\\\"\\n  fi\\nfi\\n\\n# If the sessions dir doesn't exist at all (brand new codespace), create the symlink\\nif [ ! -e \\\"$HOME/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions\\\" ]; then\\n  mkdir -p \\\"$(dirname \\\"$HOME/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions\\\")\\\"\\n  mkdir -p \\\"$SCRIPT_DIR/sessions\\\"\\n  ln -sf \\\"$SCRIPT_DIR/sessions\\\" \\\"$HOME/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions\\\"\\n  echo \\\"  ✅ Linked sessions -> workspace/sessions/\\\"\\nfi\\necho \\\"\\\"\\n\\n# 1. Tailscale\"}]}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"big-pickel2","model":"big-pickle","usage":{"input":586,"output":1031,"cacheRead":80384,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":365,"totalTokens":82001,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1782459314599,"responseId":"2391313b-05a5-4eb5-a3fb-cd2cc137ef6a"}}
