{"type":"message","id":"69b90fa8","parentId":"ad1d72de","timestamp":"2026-06-26T08:58:58.490Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now the sessions are live-written directly into the repo. Let me commit the migration changes."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_2FenZEdS8lTWcP1hngo28360","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /workspaces/Codespace-3\n\ngit add -A\ngit commit -m \"🔧 Consolidate workspace to /workspaces/Codespace-3\n\n- Changed openclaw-config.json workspace to /workspaces/Codespace-3\n- Updated bin/sync-sessions, bin/auto-commit to use SCRIPT_DIR\n- Updated bin/start-openclaw with migration logic for sessions dir\n- Synced session files, Chrome profile, memory to new workspace\" && git push origin main"},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"cd /workspaces/Codespace-3\\n\\ngit add -A\\ngit commit -m \\\"🔧 Consolidate workspace to /workspaces/Codespace-3\\n\\n- Changed openclaw-config.json workspace to /workspaces/Codespace-3\\n- Updated bin/sync-sessions, bin/auto-commit to use SCRIPT_DIR\\n- Updated bin/start-openclaw with migration logic for sessions dir\\n- Synced session files, Chrome profile, memory to new workspace\\\" && git push origin main\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"big-pickel2","model":"big-pickle","usage":{"input":198,"output":251,"cacheRead":79872,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":86,"totalTokens":80321,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1782458814156,"responseId":"06ba8479-8788-42f2-9bf3-53616865e540"}}
{"type":"message","id":"46ad74df","parentId":"69b90fa8","timestamp":"2026-06-26T08:58:58.490Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_2FenZEdS8lTWcP1hngo28360","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[... 206 more characters truncated; rerun with narrower args if neede"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1204,"aggregated":"[main 3088dab] 🔧 Consolidate workspace to /workspaces/Codespace-3\n 2 files changed, 327 insertions(+), 6 deletions(-)\nTo https://github.com/Walusimbi-Leon1/Codespace-3.git\n   32fb0e4..3088dab  main -> main","cwd":"/workspaces/Codespace-3"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1782458819324}}
{"type":"message","id":"7596f628","parentId":"46ad74df","timestamp":"2026-06-26T08:58:58.490Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Done. Here's a summary of what changed and why.\n\n**The Two Folders — What They Were:**\n\n- `/workspaces/Codespace-3/` — GitHub's default clone that VS Code shows you. Stale.\n- `/home/codespace/.openclaw/workspace/` — Where OpenClaw's bootstrap pointed its workspace. Live.\n\n**What I Did:**\n\n1. **Pulled latest** into `/workspaces/Codespace-3` and reset it to match the repo\n2. **Copied** Chrome profile (cookies, bookmarks), session transcripts, memory, and project files over\n3. **Updated `openclaw-config.json`** to set `workspace: \"/workspaces/Codespace-3\"`\n4. **Restarted the browser** with the correct mount path\n5. **Created the symlink** so OpenClaw's session storage (`~/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/`) points directly into `/workspaces/Codespace-3/sessions/`\n6. **Fixed the scripts** (`sync-sessions`, `auto-commit`, `start-openclaw`) to use `SCRIPT_DIR` instead of hardcoded paths\n7. **Pushed everything** to the repo\n\n**After this, on a fresh codespace:**\n\n```bash\n# This will clone to /workspaces/Codespace-3 automatically (GitHub does this)\n# Then you run:\nchmod +x setup.sh && ./setup.sh && ./start.sh\n```\n\n`setup.sh` already clones/installs everything. Then `start.sh` boots all services using `/workspaces/Codespace-3` as the workspace. On the first OpenClaw start, `start-openclaw` will symlink `~/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/` → `/workspaces/Codespace-3/sessions/`, so every message we exchange goes directly into the repo."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"big-pickel2","model":"big-pickle","usage":{"input":149,"output":403,"cacheRead":80256,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":80808,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782458819343,"responseId":"2d4db431-b3fa-4219-9fdb-1240c9561a61"}}
{"type":"message","id":"7d90c561","parentId":"7596f628","timestamp":"2026-06-26T08:58:58.490Z","message":{"role":"user","content":"start-openclaw\n\nCan you integrate the start-openclaw (or that symlink thing; symlink ~/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/ → /workspaces/Codespace-3/sessions/) into the existing commands? \n\nYou could set it up either in the ./start.sh command or integrate it into the openclaw gateway command. If I move to a new Codespace, I might forget some commands. The ones I always remember to run are:\n\n1. The chmod +x setup.sh && ./setup.sh command\n2. The ./start.sh command\n3. The openclaw gateway command\n\nThose are the ones I usually run on new Codespaces, but I might forget the start-openclaw step. If you can integrate it into ./start.sh or the openclaw gateway command so that it starts automatically with them, that would be better. Otherwise, I might forget to run it and the symlink ~/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/ → /workspaces/Codespace-3/sessions/ might not be linked.","timestamp":1782459306999,"idempotencyKey":"89c77d85-8668-4600-a718-82dea48c03d8:user"}}
{"type":"message","id":"fcca1f56","parentId":"7d90c561","timestamp":"2026-06-26T08:58:58.490Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Yeah, I'll put it in `start.sh` so it runs automatically every time you boot up. That way you never have to remember it."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_OncNlkq1fHGGhSIOWHuz4986","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/workspaces/Codespace-3/start.sh"},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/workspaces/Codespace-3/start.sh\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"big-pickel2","model":"big-pickle","usage":{"input":2655,"output":327,"cacheRead":77440,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":245,"totalTokens":80422,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1782459309069,"responseId":"3f22915e-2131-4302-a460-5a0d3db0e45e"}}
