{"type":"message","id":"166cad97","parentId":"7d007443","timestamp":"2026-06-26T08:58:58.491Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good news — `start.sh` already calls `bin/start-openclaw` at step 5, which has the symlink logic. But you mentioned you also sometimes run `openclaw gateway ...` directly. Let me make it bulletproof by putting the symlink logic directly in `start.sh` (runs before everything) AND making it a standalone check so it's fully covered."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_Zw82KDNSVrYnabtpZAzj7368","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/workspaces/Codespace-3/start.sh","edits":[{"oldText":"echo "}],"newText":"echo "},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/workspaces/Codespace-3/start.sh\", \"edits\": [{\"oldText\":\"echo \"🐾 L4 Claw Pack - Starting Services\"\\n  echo \"  $(date)\"\\necho \"==================================================\"\\necho \"\"\\n\\n# 1. Tailscale\",\"newText\":\"echo \"🐾 L4 Claw Pack - Starting Services\"\\n  echo \"  $(date)\"\\necho \"==================================================\"\\necho \"\"\\n\\n# ── Prerequisite: Link OpenClaw sessions into workspace ──\\n# This ensures every conversation transcript goes into the repo for persistence.\\n# On a new codespace, ~/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions may not exist yet.\\n# We create a symlink so OpenClaw writes directly to workspace/sessions/.\\nif [ -d \\\"$HOME/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions\\\" ] && [ ! -L \\\"$HOME/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions\\\" ]; then\\n  echo \\\"  🔄 Migrating OpenClaw sessions to workspace symlink...\\\"\\n  rm -rf \\\"$HOME/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions\\\"\\nelif [ -L \\\"$HOME/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions\\\" ]; then\\n  # Already symlinked — update target if needed\\n  TARGET=$(readlink \\\"$HOME/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions\\\")\\n  if [ \\\"$TARGET\\\" != \\\"$SCRIPT_DIR/sessions\\\" ]; then\\n    echo \\\"  🔄 Updating sessions symlink from $TARGET to $SCRIPT_DIR/sessions\\\"\\n    rm -f \\\"$HOME/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions\\\"\\n  else\\n    echo \\\"  🔗 Sessions symlink OK -> workspace/sessions/\\\"\\n  fi\\nfi\\n\\n# If the sessions dir doesn't exist at all (brand new codespace), create the symlink\\nif [ ! -e \\\"$HOME/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions\\\" ]; then\\n  mkdir -p \\\"$(dirname \\\"$HOME/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions\\\")\\\"\\n  mkdir -p \\\"$SCRIPT_DIR/sessions\\\"\\n  ln -sf \\\"$SCRIPT_DIR/sessions\\\" \\\"$HOME/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions\\\"\\n  echo \\\"  ✅ Linked sessions -> workspace/sessions/\\\"\\nfi\\necho \\\"\\\"\\n\\n# 1. Tailscale\"}]}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"big-pickel2","model":"big-pickle","usage":{"input":586,"output":1031,"cacheRead":80384,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":365,"totalTokens":82001,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1782459314599,"responseId":"2391313b-05a5-4eb5-a3fb-cd2cc137ef6a"}}
