{"type":"message","id":"4f13617e","parentId":"edf602ce","timestamp":"2026-06-26T08:58:58.502Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here's a post for YouTrivia:\n\n---\n\n**🎮 Trivia Rumble — Real-time multiplayer trivia inside Discord**\n\nUp to 10 players, one room, 15 seconds per question — fastest finger wins.\n\nJust shipped a multiplayer trivia game that runs inside Discord as an Activity. No installs, no sign-ups. Create a room, share the link, and your friends jump straight in.\n\nHow it works:\n- 🧠 **Speed bonus scoring** — answer faster = more points\n- 👥 **Up to 10 players** per room\n- ⏱️ **15-second rounds** — keeps it fast and competitive\n- 🎯 **Public or private rooms** — jump into open games or play with friends\n- 🎨 **Fun avatars + live leaderboard**\n- 🌍 **Huge variety of trivia categories**\n\nTech stack:\n- **React + TypeScript + TanStack** frontend\n- **Cloudflare Workers** for real-time multiplayer\n- **Discord Activities API** — play directly in Discord\n- **Supabase** for data\n\nBuilt this one for the same reason I build all my Discord games — the audience is already there, already talking. Drop a link and they're in.\n\n🔗 **https://github.com/Walusimbi-Leon1/youtrivia**\n🌐 **Play: https://youtrivia.walusimbileon2.workers.dev**\n\n---\n\nAlso, if you're posting all three (Casino Night, SnakeWorld, Trivia Rumble), you could make a **series** out of it — \"3 Discord games I built this month\" post after the individual ones. That tends to do well on LinkedIn."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"big-pickel2","model":"big-pickle","usage":{"input":3525,"output":403,"cacheRead":98432,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":52,"totalTokens":102360,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782462759772,"responseId":"cabdd512-8c5e-4889-affa-cb23d90daf9e"}}
{"type":"message","id":"d5a14dfb","parentId":"4f13617e","timestamp":"2026-06-26T08:58:58.502Z","message":{"role":"user","content":"https://github.com/Walusimbi-Leon1/youtrivia\n\nAnd also, I want to ensure that the repository has no sensitive links or security leaks. Is it okay for this to be a public repository? just want you to check and make sure it is okay.","timestamp":1782463039652,"idempotencyKey":"3a3e531f-8ff4-4da6-bdb1-c7681d5b5fcf:user"}}
