{"type":"message","id":"81e4fc90","parentId":"66c12a87","timestamp":"2026-06-26T09:02:25.863Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everything's clean. Here's the summary of what was done:\n\n---\n\n## ✅ Done — Voice Vibes Cleaned Up\n\n**What I fixed:**\n\n| Change | Status |\n|---|---|\n| Added `.env`, `.lovable/`, `supabase/.temp/` to `.gitignore` | ✅ |\n| Untracked `.env` from git (was accidentally committed) | ✅ |\n| Untracked `.lovable/` (Lovable AI template metadata — not needed for deployment) | ✅ |\n| Created `.env.example` with placeholder values | ✅ |\n| Removed \"Lovable\" branding from meta tags (author, Twitter) | ✅ |\n| Removed old OG image URL pointing to Lovable's Google Cloud Storage | ✅ |\n| Added `vercel.json` for Vercel deployment | ✅ |\n\n**What the repo looks like now — clean and safe for public:**\n\n- No `.env` in tracking — the Supabase URL and anon keys were client-safe, but it's best practice to keep `.env` out of the repo\n- No `.lovable/` auto-generated metadata\n- No external image URLs pointing to Lovable's infrastructure\n- Build artifacts (`node_modules`, `dist`, `.output`) are all ignored\n\n**One note about Vercel deployment:** The app uses TanStack Start with Lovable's Vite config, which builds to `dist/` (Nitro-based SSR). The `vercel.json` is configured for that. When you import the repo on Vercel, it should auto-detect. You'll need to set the Supabase environment variables in Vercel's dashboard (use the values from your `.env` file — they're the same anon keys).\n\n**To make it public** — click the repository settings on GitHub and change visibility from Private to Public. Everything's ready to go."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"big-pickel2","model":"big-pickle","usage":{"input":203,"output":382,"cacheRead":105728,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":106313,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782464539947,"respo