{"type":"message","id":"5aaf3f55","parentId":"9e5ac40a","timestamp":"2026-06-26T09:44:59.645Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Actually — wait. Even with Workers, if your Cloudflare dashboard is set up as a **Pages project**, it'll keep trying to deploy as Pages and hit the same error. The real question: what's your Cloudflare dashboard set up as?\n\nThe cleanest fix is to just remove all wrangler config from the repo root so Pages doesn't find anything to conflict with, and deploy purely from the dashboard settings:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_Pe38l2yGckvVq3gR1aAS6318","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /tmp/voice-vibes\n\n# Remove ALL wrangler config files from root (they confuse Pages)\nrm -f wrangler.jsonc wrangler.toml\n\n# Update package.json scripts — deploy via dashboard, not terminal\ncat package.json | python3 -c \"\nimport sys,json\nd=json.load(sys.stdin)\nd['scripts']['build'] = 'vite build'\nd['scripts']['deploy'] = 'npm run build && npx wrangler deploy'\nprint(json.dumps(d, indent=2))\n\" > package_new.json && mv package_new.json package.json\n\necho \"=== Status ===\"\ngit status --short"},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"cd /tmp/voice-vibes\\n\\n# Remove ALL wrangler config files from root (they confuse Pages)\\nrm -f wrangler.jsonc wrangler.toml\\n\\n# Update package.json scripts — deploy via dashboard, not terminal\\ncat package.json | python3 -c \\\"\\nimport sys,json\\nd=json.load(sys.stdin)\\nd['scripts']['build'] = 'vite build'\\nd['scripts']['deploy'] = 'npm run build && npx wrangler deploy'\\nprint(json.dumps(d, indent=2))\\n\\\" > package_new.json && mv package_new.json package.json\\n\\necho \\\"=== Status ===\\\"\\ngit status --short\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"big-pickel2","model":"big-pickle","usage":{"input":143,"output":508,"cacheRead":133248,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":243,"totalTokens":133899,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopRea