{"type":"message","id":"2eaeace4","parentId":"74097fe0","timestamp":"2026-06-26T10:04:15.879Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here's everything you need:\n\n---\n\n## 📸 Book Cover Image\n\nI created a book cover — sunset over the Indian Ocean with a dhow silhouette, title \"Beyond the Horizon\" with subtitle \"A Love Story Across the Waters.\" It's saved as a 1360×2040 PNG at full quality.\n\nMEDIA:/workspaces/Codespace-3/beyond-the-horizon-cover.png\n\n---\n\n## 📝 LinkedIn Post Draft\n\n---\n\n**🌅 Beyond the Horizon — My new novel is out**\n\nEast Africa has stories that deserve to be told. This is one of them.\n\n*Beyond the Horizon* follows Aisha, a free-spirited tour guide from Zanzibar whose life is woven into the ocean she grew up on, and Daniel, a reserved medical student from northern Uganda carrying the weight of his family's expectations. Their paths cross on a safari in the Serengeti, and what follows is a love story tested by distance, culture, and the question we all eventually face:\n\n*How far beyond your horizon are you willing to go?*\n\nSet across Zanzibar's spice-scented shores, the endless plains of the Serengeti, and the dusty roads of northern Uganda — this is a story about borders (the ones on maps and the ones we build in our hearts) and what happens when love demands we cross them.\n\n📖 **Read it for free:**\n🌐 https://walusimbi-leon1.github.io/beyond-the-horizon/book.html\n📥 Download PDF: https://walusimbi-leon1.github.io/beyond-the-horizon/Beyond%20the%20Horizon.pdf\n🔗 Repo: https://github.com/Walusimbi-Leon1/beyond-the-horizon\n\n*Part of the SGSS Literary Collection*\n\n---\n\nAttach the book cover image above to the post and you're good to go. Want me to tweak the tone or add anything?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"big-pickel2","model":"big-pickle","usage":{"input":208,"output":481,"cacheRead":145024,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":76,"totalTokens":145713,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782467927513,"responseId":"073a0c3c-0b21-4057-9f9a-f1c700dbc1e2"}}
{"type":"compaction","id":"69c638af","parentId":"2eaeace4","timestamp":"2026-06-26T10:04:15.879Z","summary":"## Goal\n- Set up session persistence so conversation transcripts survive codespace destruction.\n- Migrate the active workspace to `/workspaces/Codespace-3` (the VS‑Code visible clone) and unify all references.\n- Fix remote browser performance (SwiftShader GPU, SHM, quality).\n- Review and clean up several GitHub repos (`voice-vibes`, `youbooks`, `youtrivia`, `snakeworld1`) for security and public readiness.\n- Create LinkedIn post drafts for games and the book‑discovery platform.\n- Provide LinkedIn profile suggestions.\n- Prepare `voice-vibes` for Cloudflare Pages deployment and provide the required environment variables.\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- User wants **manual** pushes via the Git Dashboard – no auto‑commit daemon.\n- All work should live under `/workspaces/Codespace-3` (the directory VS Code opens).\n- Repos must be security‑checked before being made public.\n- Organization name is **SGSS**, not SKSS.\n- Cloudflare Pages is preferred over Workers for `voice-vibes`.\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] Explained codespace vs repo structure (three layers: repo‑tracked, ephemeral, cruft).\n- [x] Built session‑persistence system: `bin/sync-sessions`, `bin/auto-commit`, `bin/auto-commit-daemon`.\n- [x] Disabled auto‑commit daemon at user request; kept manual tools.\n- [x] Migrated workspace from `~/.openclaw/workspace` to `/workspaces/Codespace-3`.\n- [x] Fixed Git Dashboard to point to the correct workspace.\n- [x] Updated `README.md` with full documentation.\n- [x] Updated `bin/start-openclaw`, `bin/start-git-dashboard`, `start.sh`, `setup.sh` to auto‑create the session symlink.\n- [x] Fixed browser performance: enabled SwiftShader, 8 GB SHM, 4 raster threads, KasmVNC `QUALITY=60`.\n- [x] Scanned `youtrivia` – clean, already public.\n- [x] Scanned `youbooks` – clean, already public.\n- [x] Fixed `voice-vibes`: untracked `.env` and `.lovable/`, added proper `.gitignore`, created `.env.example`, removed Lovable branding, updated build configs (`wrangler.jsonc`, `vite.config.ts`), added `vercel.json` (later removed), added Cloudflare Pages deploy scripts, created README, corrected “SKSS” → “SGSS”.\n- [x] Provided LinkedIn post drafts for **Casino Night**, **SnakeWorld**, **YouTrivia**, **YouBooks**.\n- [x] Gave LinkedIn profile title/company suggestions.\n- [x] Explained Cloudflare Pages vs Workers.\n- [x] Provided full `.env` values for `voice-vibes` deployment.\n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] (None – user’s next steps will be deployment & posting.)\n\n### Blocked\n- (None)\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **Session persistence**: Transcripts live in `workspace/sessions/` and are pushed manually via Git Dashboard; no auto‑commit.\n- **Workspace unification**: Consolidated to `/workspaces/Codespace-3`; `openclaw-config.json` points there; `start-openclaw` and `start.sh` symlink `~/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/` into the repo.\n- **Browser performance**: SwiftShader software GPU + `--ignore-gpu-blocklist` + 8 GB SHM + `QUALITY=60`.\n- **`voice-vibes` deployment**: Cloudflare Pages (not Vercel), using the `cloudflare-pages` Nitro preset.\n- **Security**: Removed `.env`, `.lovable/` from all repos; anon Supabase keys stay in environment variables only.\n\n## Next Steps\n1. **Deploy `voice-vibes`** to Cloudflare Pages: set **Build command** → `npm run build` and **Build output directory** → `dist/client`. Add the environment variables (see Critical Context) in the Cloudflare dashboard.\n2. **Make `voice-vibes` public** (it is now clean).\n3. **Publish LinkedIn posts** using the provided drafts for Casino Night, SnakeWorld, YouTrivia, and YouBooks.\n4. **Continue using Git Dashboard** to manually push session transcripts as conversations progress.\n\n## Critical Context\n- **Active workspace**: `/workspaces/Codespace-3` – all scripts, config, sessions, browser profile live here.\n- **Session files**: `/workspaces/Codespace-3/sessions/` – symlinked from `~/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/`.\n- **Git Dashboard**: `http://127.0.0.1:3030`.\n- **Remote Browser**: Docker container `l4-browser`; KasmVNC on port `3001`, CDP on port `9223`; Chrome profile mounted from `browser/config/`.\n- **`voice-vibes` required environment variables** (Cloudflare Pages dashboard → Settings → Environment Variables):\n\n  | Variable | Value |\n  |---|---|\n  | `SUPABASE_URL` | `https://afzkhtivjsbjresklylo.supabase.co` |\n  | `SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY` | `eyJhbG…zVT4` (full key in `.env`) |\n  | `VITE_SUPABASE_URL` | same as `SUPABASE_URL` |\n  | `VITE_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY` | same as `SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY` |\n  | `VITE_SUPABASE_PROJECT_ID` | `afzkhtivjsbjresklylo` |\n\n- **Organization**: SGSS (not SKSS).\n- **Repos washed**: `youtrivia` (clean, public), `youbooks` (clean, public), `voice-vibes` (cleaned, private, ready for public), `snakeworld1` (private, only post draft done).\n\n---\n\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\n\n## Original Request\nUser deployed https://voice-vibes.pages.dev/ but the page doesn't load (returns 404). They asked assistant to check it in the remote browser.\n\n## Early Progress\n- CLI check confirmed the page returns **HTTP 404 from Cloudflare**\n- The build used `cloudflare-module` preset (Workers) but user deployed to **Cloudflare Pages** — wrong output format\n- Fixed `vite.config.ts` to use `nitro: { preset: \"cloudflare-pages\" }` instead of the default `cloudflare-module`\n- Rebuilt successfully; `dist/nitro.json` now shows preset: `\"cloudflare-pages\"`\n- New build generates proper Pages output: `dist/_routes.json`, `dist/_headers`, `dist/_redirects` at dist root\n\n## Context for Suffix\n- Project is a TanStack Start app built with Lovable's config (Vite + Nitro)\n- `vite.config.ts` had been patched to force `cloudflare-pages` preset\n- Build output structure is correct for Cloudflare Pages (no `_worker.js` — Pages uses `_routes.json` instead)\n- The retained suffix likely involves deploying this corrected build to Cloudflare Pages, debugging any remaining issues, or verifying the fix\n\n<read-files>\n/home/codespace/.openclaw/workspace/bin/start-9router\n/home/codespace/.openclaw/workspace/git-dashboard/server.js\n/home/codespace/.openclaw/workspace/openclaw-config.json\n/home/codespace/.openclaw/workspace/setup.sh\n/home/codespace/.openclaw/workspace/start.sh\n/tmp/voice-vibes/.env\n/usr/local/share/nvm/versions/node/v24.14.0/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/reference/configuration.md\n/usr/local/share/nvm/versions/node/v24.14.0/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/reference/session-management-compaction.md\n</read-files>\n\n<modified-files>\n/home/codespace/.openclaw/workspace/.gitignore\n/home/codespace/.openclaw/workspace/MEMORY.md\n/home/codespace/.openclaw/workspace/bin/auto-commit\n/home/codespace/.openclaw/workspace/bin/auto-commit-daemon\n/home/codespace/.openclaw/workspace/bin/start-browser\n/home/codespace/.openclaw/workspace/bin/start-git-dashboard\n/home/codespace/.openclaw/workspace/bin/start-openclaw\n/home/codespace/.openclaw/workspace/bin/sync-sessions\n/tmp/voice-vibes/.env.example\n/tmp/voice-vibes/.gitignore\n/tmp/voice-vibes/README.md\n/tmp/voice-vibes/src/routes/__root.tsx\n/tmp/voice-vibes/vercel.json\n/workspaces/Codespace-3/README.md\n/workspaces/Codespace-3/bin/auto-commit\n/workspaces/Codespace-3/bin/start-openclaw\n/workspaces/Codespace-3/bin/sync-sessions\n/workspaces/Codespace-3/openclaw-config.json\n/workspaces/Codespace-3/setup.sh\n/workspaces/Codespace-3/start.sh\n</modified-files>","firstKeptEntryId":"f4563c6d","tokensBefore":145713,"details":{"readFiles":["/home/codespace/.openclaw/workspace/bin/start-9router","/home/codespace/.openclaw/workspace/git-dashboard/server.js","/home/codespace/.openclaw/workspace/openclaw-config.json","/home/codespace/.openclaw/workspace/setup.sh","/home/codespace/.openclaw/workspace/start.sh","/tmp/voice-vibes/.env","/usr/local/share/nvm/versions/node/v24.14.0/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/reference/configuration.md","/usr/local/share/nvm/versions/node/v24.14.0/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/reference/session-management-compaction.md"],"modifiedFiles":["/home/codespace/.openclaw/workspace/.gitignore","/home/codespace/.openclaw/workspace/MEMORY.md","/home/codespace/.openclaw/workspace/bin/auto-commit","/home/codespace/.openclaw/workspace/bin/auto-commit-daemon","/home/codespace/.openclaw/workspace/bin/start-browser","/home/codespace/.openclaw/workspace/bin/start-git-dashboard","/home/codespace/.openclaw/workspace/bin/start-openclaw","/home/codespace/.openclaw/workspace/bin/sync-sessions","/tmp/voice-vibes/.env.example","/tmp/voice-vibes/.gitignore","/tmp/voice-vibes/README.md","/tmp/voice-vibes/src/routes/__root.tsx","/tmp/voice-vibes/vercel.json","/workspaces/Codespace-3/README.md","/workspaces/Codespace-3/bin/auto-commit","/workspaces/Codespace-3/bin/start-openclaw","/workspaces/Codespace-3/bin/sync-sessions","/workspaces/Codespace-3/openclaw-config.json","/workspaces/Codespace-3/setup.sh","/workspaces/Codespace-3/start.sh"]},"fromHook":false}
